<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
{{ head_extras | safe }}
<style id="canonical-body-css">
/* ─── Site-wide horizontal anchor ─── */
/* Locks the document horizontally so no page can be panned sideways on
   mobile. Without this, any element that accidentally exceeds viewport
   width (a wide chart container, a long word, a misconfigured grid,
   etc.) lets the entire page slide left/right under finger gestures,
   which reads as a layout bug. Observed on /heatmap and
   /bitcoin-vs-the-stock-market before this rule was added.
   `clip` is preferred over `hidden` because it doesn't create a new
   scroll context and doesn't break `position: sticky` descendants;
   widely supported in modern browsers. Applied to both html and body
   for belt-and-suspenders coverage across user-agent quirks. */
html, body {
    overflow-x: clip;
}

/* ─── Site-wide body invariants ─── */
/* Source of truth for body font-family, size, and line-height.
   Every page inherits these unless it deliberately overrides
   (e.g. cream-bg essay pages would set font-family: EB Garamond
   in their page_styles, which load AFTER this block and win by
   source order). Pages still set their own body { background, color }
   to match their palette — those properties merge with the rules
   here. See STYLE_GUIDE.md §1 'Site-wide <body> rule' and §2.3
   'Site-wide body invariants' for rationale. Without this default,
   pages that omit a body { font-family } rule fall back to browser-
   default Times New Roman — a failure mode that shipped on DR for
   months before being caught. */
body {
    font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
    -moz-osx-font-smoothing: grayscale;
}
</style>
<style id="canonical-nav-css">
/* ─── Canonical nav (mobile + desktop) ─── */
/* Source of truth for site-nav, hamburger, mobile-overlay, nav-dropdown.
   Per-page CSS may override specific properties when there's a deliberate
   design reason (e.g. calc-tier pages use a different overlay style).
   Per-page rules come AFTER this block in <head> via page_styles, so they
   win by source order. */
.site-nav { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; padding: 12px 24px; background: rgba(10,9,8,0.95); border-bottom: 1px solid #1a1a1a; position: sticky; top: 0; z-index: 1000; backdrop-filter: blur(12px); -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(12px); }
.site-nav .brand { font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, sans-serif; font-size: 0.8rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.18em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #999; text-decoration: none; transition: color 0.2s; }
.site-nav .brand:hover { color: #e09422; }
.site-nav .nav-links { display: flex; gap: 8px; align-items: center; }
.site-nav .nav-links a { font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, sans-serif; font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 500; color: #aaa; text-decoration: none; padding: 8px 16px; border-radius: 4px; transition: color 0.2s, background 0.2s; }
.site-nav .nav-links a:hover { color: #ccc; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04); }
.site-nav .nav-links a.active { color: #e09422; background: rgba(247,147,26,0.08); font-weight: 600; }
.hamburger { display: none; background: none; border: none; cursor: pointer; padding: 4px; z-index: 1100; }
.hamburger span { display: block; width: 22px; height: 2px; background: #aaa; margin: 5px 0; border-radius: 1px; transition: transform 0.3s, opacity 0.3s, background 0.3s; }
.hamburger:hover span { background: #ccc; }
.hamburger.open span:nth-child(1) { transform: rotate(45deg) translate(5px, 5px); }
.hamburger.open span:nth-child(2) { opacity: 0; }
.hamburger.open span:nth-child(3) { transform: rotate(-45deg) translate(5px, -5px); }
.mobile-overlay { display: none; position: fixed; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; background: rgba(10,9,8,0.97); z-index: 1050; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; justify-content: flex-start; gap: 8px; opacity: 0; transition: opacity 0.3s; padding: 4.5rem 1rem 2.5rem; overflow-y: auto; -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch; }
.mobile-overlay.show { display: flex; opacity: 1; }
.mobile-overlay a { font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, sans-serif; font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 500; color: #aaa; text-decoration: none; padding: 14px 32px; border-radius: 6px; transition: color 0.2s, background 0.2s; }
.mobile-overlay a:hover { color: #ccc; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04); }
.mobile-overlay a.active { color: #e09422; background: rgba(247,147,26,0.08); font-weight: 600; }
.nav-dropdown { position: relative; display: inline-block; }
.nav-dropdown-btn { cursor: pointer; user-select: none; }
.nav-dropdown-menu { display: none; position: absolute; top: 100%; left: 50%; transform: translateX(-50%); background: rgba(10,9,8,0.97); border: 1px solid rgba(247,147,26,0.15); border-radius: 8px; padding: 8px 0; min-width: 240px; z-index: 200; backdrop-filter: blur(12px); box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(0,0,0,0.4); margin-top: 0; }
.nav-dropdown:hover .nav-dropdown-menu, .nav-dropdown.open .nav-dropdown-menu { display: block; }
.nav-dropdown-menu a { display: block; padding: 9px 24px; font-size: 0.88rem; white-space: nowrap; color: #aaa; text-decoration: none; transition: color 0.2s, background 0.2s; }
.nav-dropdown-menu a:hover { color: #ccc; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04); }
.nav-dropdown-menu a.active { color: #e09422; background: rgba(247,147,26,0.08); font-weight: 600; }
.nav-dropdown-legend { font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, sans-serif; font-size: 0.7rem; font-style: italic; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.4); padding: 8px 24px 4px; margin-top: 4px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06); white-space: nowrap; }
.mobile-legend { font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, sans-serif; font-size: 0.78rem; font-style: italic; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.42); padding: 1.6rem 32px 0; margin-top: 0.6rem; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06); }
.nav-interactive-marker { color: #e09422; font-size: 0.7em; opacity: 0.7; margin-left: 2px; line-height: 1; vertical-align: 0.05em; }
.mobile-section-label { font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, sans-serif; font-size: 0.65rem; font-weight: 600; color: #888; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.18em; margin: 0.9rem 0 0.2rem; padding: 0 32px; }
.mobile-section-label:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .site-nav .nav-links { display: none; }
  .hamburger { display: block; }
}
</style>
<style id="canonical-typography-css">
/* ─── Site-wide heading typography invariants ─── */
/* Single rule applied to every page: text-wrap: balance distributes  */
/* heading content across lines to avoid orphan words and awkward     */
/* greedy wraps on mobile. Per-page CSS still controls font-family    */
/* and font-size; this only handles line-balancing. Progressive       */
/* enhancement — pre-2024 browsers fall back to default greedy wrap   */
/* without visual regression. See STYLE_GUIDE.md §2.1 for the         */
/* canonical h1/h2/h3 size scale this complements.                    */
h1, h2, h3 {
  text-wrap: balance;
}
</style>
{%- if page_styles %}
    <style>
{{ page_styles | safe }}
    </style>
{%- endif %}
<style id="canonical-footer-css">
/* ─── Canonical footer ─── */
.site-footer { background: #0a0908; padding: 4rem 2rem 3rem; text-align: center; border-top: 1px solid rgba(224,148,34,0.08); margin-top: 4rem; }
.site-footer .footer-cta { max-width: 540px; margin: 0 auto; }
.site-footer .footer-cta h3 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.6rem; font-weight: 500; color: #ece4d6; margin: 0 0 0.9rem; }
.site-footer .footer-cta p { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: 0.85rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.42); line-height: 1.6; margin: 0 0 2.4rem; }
.site-footer .footer-nav { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr)); gap: 1.5rem 2rem; max-width: 960px; margin: 0 auto 2.6rem; text-align: left; }
.site-footer .footer-nav-section { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.55rem; }
.site-footer .footer-nav-label { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: 0.65rem; font-weight: 600; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.55); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.16em; margin-bottom: 0.35rem; }
.site-footer .footer-nav a { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: 0.72rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.36); text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 0.06em; text-transform: uppercase; transition: color 0.3s; border-bottom: none; }
.site-footer .footer-nav a:hover { color: #e09422; }
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .site-footer .footer-nav { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr)); text-align: left; }
}
/* ─── Footer tip block (Lightning Address) — restrained presence, click-to-copy ─── */
.site-footer .footer-tip { max-width: 540px; margin: 0 auto 2.4rem; text-align: center; padding: 0 1rem; }
.site-footer .footer-tip-copy { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: 0.78rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.45); line-height: 1.6; margin: 0 0 0.9rem; letter-spacing: 0.01em; font-style: italic; }
.site-footer .footer-tip-address { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; padding: 0.55rem 1.1rem; background: rgba(247,147,26,0.06); border: 1px solid rgba(247,147,26,0.20); border-radius: 999px; font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', 'SF Mono', Menlo, Consolas, monospace; font-size: 0.78rem; color: #e09422; text-decoration: none; transition: background 0.3s, border-color 0.3s, color 0.3s; cursor: pointer; user-select: none; }
.site-footer .footer-tip-address:hover { background: rgba(247,147,26,0.12); border-color: rgba(247,147,26,0.35); color: #F7931A; }
.site-footer .footer-tip-bolt { font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 1; }
.site-footer .footer-tip-address.copied { background: rgba(247,147,26,0.16); border-color: rgba(247,147,26,0.45); color: #F7931A; }
.site-footer .footer-tip-qr { display: inline-block; margin: 1.15rem auto 0.55rem; padding: 9px; background: rgba(247,147,26,0.03); border: 1px solid rgba(247,147,26,0.15); border-radius: 8px; line-height: 0; }
.site-footer .footer-tip-qr svg { display: block; width: 112px; height: 112px; }
.site-footer .footer-tip-caption { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: 0.62rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.32); letter-spacing: 0.16em; text-transform: uppercase; margin: 0; }
.site-footer .footer-line { width: 40px; height: 1px; background: rgba(224,148,34,0.3); margin: 0 auto 1.4rem; }
.site-footer .footer-copy { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: 0.7rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.22); letter-spacing: 0.04em; }

/* ─── Related component (cross-reference cards) — see STYLE_GUIDE §6.10 ─── */
.related-block { max-width: 1100px; margin: 4rem auto 2rem; padding: 2.4rem 2rem 0; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06); }
.related-label { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: 0.62rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.18em; text-transform: uppercase; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.42); margin-bottom: 1.4rem; }
.related-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap: 1rem; }
.related-card { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.5rem; padding: 1.25rem 1.4rem; background: #111110; border: 1px solid #1e1c1a; border-radius: 0.5rem; text-decoration: none; color: inherit; transition: border-color 0.25s, transform 0.25s; position: relative; overflow: hidden; }
.related-card:hover { border-color: rgba(247,147,26,0.28); transform: translateY(-2px); }
.related-card::before { content: ''; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; right: 0; height: 2px; background: #F7931A; opacity: 0; transition: opacity 0.25s; }
.related-card:hover::before { opacity: 1; }

/* ─── Layout-level "Share this page" — see STYLE_GUIDE §6.26 ─── */
/* Auto-injected by base.njk between page content and the footer on
   every page (unless frontmatter sets share_in_layout: false). The URL
   shared is window.location.origin + pathname + hash — no query params,
   so scenario state on calculator pages is intentionally stripped. The
   in-page two-group share section on those pages remains the place for
   "Share this scenario" (it keeps query params); this layout-level
   surface is purely page-promotion.
   Visual treatment matches the canonical-footer register: dim border-
   top, restrained palette, centered, single-row pill buttons. Portable
   rgba() colors so the block works on every page palette (most are
   dark; cream-bg essay pages can override .page-share rules in their
   page_styles if they ever ship). */
.page-share { max-width: 1100px; margin: 3rem auto 0; padding: 2rem 2rem 0; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06); text-align: center; }
.page-share-eyebrow { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: 0.62rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.18em; text-transform: uppercase; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.42); margin-bottom: 1rem; }
.page-share-actions { display: inline-flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.55rem; justify-content: center; }
.page-share-btn { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.45rem; padding: 0.5rem 0.95rem; background: rgba(247,147,26,0.05); border: 1px solid rgba(247,147,26,0.20); border-radius: 999px; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: 0.78rem; line-height: 1; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.6); text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer; transition: background 0.25s, border-color 0.25s, color 0.25s; }
.page-share-btn:hover, .page-share-btn:focus-visible { background: rgba(247,147,26,0.12); border-color: rgba(247,147,26,0.40); color: #F7931A; outline: none; }
.page-share-btn:active { transform: translateY(1px); }
.page-share-btn .page-share-icon { flex-shrink: 0; }
.page-share-btn.copied { background: rgba(247,147,26,0.16); border-color: rgba(247,147,26,0.45); color: #F7931A; }
.page-share-btn[hidden] { display: none; }
@media (max-width: 540px) {
  .page-share { padding: 1.6rem 1rem 0; }
  .page-share-btn { padding: 0.5rem 0.8rem; font-size: 0.74rem; }
}
@media print {
  .page-share { display: none; }
}

/* ─── USD methodology footnote — see /about.html#why-usd ─── */
/* Small inline reference link used on calculator pages where dollar
   amounts are prominent. Editorial-tier callout, not a banner. The
   message addresses non-US readers directly without disrupting the
   primary interaction; placement is just above the in-page share
   section so it sits at the calculator's natural pause point. The
   arrow link follows the site's "→ Read more" convention. */
.usd-footnote {
  text-align: center;
  font-size: 0.82rem;
  font-style: italic;
  color: rgba(255,255,255,0.42);
  margin: 1.75rem 0 0;
  line-height: 1.6;
}
.usd-footnote a {
  color: #e09422;
  text-decoration: none;
  border-bottom: 1px dotted rgba(224,148,34,0.35);
  padding-bottom: 1px;
  transition: color 0.2s, border-color 0.2s;
}
.usd-footnote a:hover, .usd-footnote a:focus-visible {
  color: #F7931A;
  border-bottom-color: rgba(224,148,34,0.8);
  outline: none;
}
@media print {
  .usd-footnote { display: none; }
}
.related-kind-marker { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: 0.6rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase; color: rgba(224,148,34,0.7); margin-bottom: 0.1rem; }
.related-card.external .related-kind-marker { color: rgba(224,148,34,0.85); }
.related-interactive-marker { color: #e09422; font-size: 0.85em; opacity: 0.85; margin-left: 1px; vertical-align: 0.05em; }
.related-card-title { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', Georgia, serif; font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.2; color: #f2eee8; margin: 0; }
.related-card-desc { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.55; color: #c8c2b8; margin: 0.2rem 0 0; }
.related-card-cta { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: 0.72rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.06em; color: #F7931A; margin-top: 0.5rem; }
@media (max-width: 720px) {
  .related-block { padding: 1.8rem 1.25rem 0; margin-top: 3rem; }
  .related-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
}

/* ─── Tool-framing strip (collapsible disclaimer) — see STYLE_GUIDE §6.11 ─── */
.tool-framing { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto 1.6rem; padding: 0 2rem; font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, sans-serif; }
.tool-framing-collapsed, .tool-framing-expanded { display: none; }
.tool-framing[data-state="collapsed"] .tool-framing-collapsed { display: block; }
.tool-framing[data-state="expanded"] .tool-framing-expanded { display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 1rem; }
.tool-framing-toggle { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; background: transparent; border: 1px solid rgba(224,148,34,0.18); border-radius: 4px; padding: 0.5rem 0.85rem; font-family: inherit; font-size: 0.78rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.55); cursor: pointer; transition: border-color 0.2s, color 0.2s, background 0.2s; }
.tool-framing-toggle:hover { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.8); border-color: rgba(224,148,34,0.4); background: rgba(224,148,34,0.04); }
.tool-framing-icon { color: #e09422; font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1; opacity: 0.85; }
.tool-framing-collapsed-text { letter-spacing: 0.02em; }
.tool-framing-expanded { background: rgba(224,148,34,0.04); border: 1px solid rgba(224,148,34,0.18); border-radius: 4px; padding: 0.95rem 1.1rem 0.95rem 1.2rem; }
.tool-framing-content { flex: 1; }
.tool-framing-label { font-size: 0.62rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.18em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #e09422; margin-bottom: 0.35rem; }
.tool-framing-body { font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); margin: 0; }
.tool-framing-dismiss { flex: 0 0 auto; background: transparent; border: none; padding: 0; margin: -2px -4px 0 0; font-size: 1.4rem; line-height: 1; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.4); cursor: pointer; transition: color 0.2s; font-family: inherit; }
.tool-framing-dismiss:hover { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.8); }
@media (max-width: 720px) {
  .tool-framing { padding: 0 1.25rem; }
  .tool-framing-body { font-size: 0.82rem; }
}

/* ─── Companion-content (off-site deep-dives) — see STYLE_GUIDE §6.12 ─── */
.companion-block { max-width: 1100px; margin: 2rem auto 1rem; padding: 1.6rem 2rem 0; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.04); }
.companion-label { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: 0.6rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.18em; text-transform: uppercase; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.36); margin-bottom: 1rem; }
.companion-list { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.6rem; }
.companion-item { display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 1rem; padding: 0.9rem 1rem; background: transparent; border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06); border-radius: 0.4rem; text-decoration: none; color: inherit; transition: border-color 0.2s, background 0.2s; }
.companion-item:hover { border-color: rgba(224,148,34,0.3); background: rgba(224,148,34,0.02); }
.companion-kind { flex: 0 0 auto; min-width: 78px; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: 0.62rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase; color: rgba(224,148,34,0.7); padding-top: 0.18rem; }
.companion-arrow { display: inline-block; margin-left: 0.15rem; opacity: 0.7; }
.companion-text { flex: 1; min-width: 0; }
.companion-title { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', Georgia, serif; font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.3; color: #f2eee8; margin: 0; }
.companion-desc { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: 0.8rem; line-height: 1.5; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.55); margin: 0.25rem 0 0; }
@media (max-width: 720px) {
  .companion-block { padding: 1.2rem 1.25rem 0; }
  .companion-item { flex-direction: column; gap: 0.4rem; padding: 0.85rem 0.95rem; }
  .companion-kind { padding-top: 0; }
}
</style>
</head>
